    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-01-27T22:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-01-27T22:00:00-05:00" n="640"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d640">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.51/7739: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Gauss</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Chungking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-01-28T10:00:00+07:00"
                            >January 28, 1944—10 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received January 28—8:35 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>181. President’s message to Chiang has been transmitted with request that Chiang
                    indicate to whom he desires that we submit our proposals regarding Army
                    financing. This refers to your 108, January 20 and 125, January 24. This
                    procedure adopted in hope proposals can be presented through and studied by some
                    one other than Chiang and not result in immediate rejection. In agreement with
                    Dr. Ache-son, the Somervell–Clay proposals first [will] be submitted in order
                    finally to dispose of their view that Chinese have committed themselves to some
                    such arrangement. Developments will be reported.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Gauss</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
